{
  "stem": "1363.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I know that my auntie and I have tried to go and rob a few shops, which was, at that day, [LAUGHS] if you didn't go to a shop to pinch something-- there was nobody at the counter.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, you went just to get food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- So, by this stage you were united, the four of you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The four of us, Grandma, Auntie, the little one, and myself.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, well, the joy was that I-- that whatever, whoever, survived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the pain was very much that my brother didn't.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That is a great-- because that I lost my father, and I lost my mother, [SIGHS] but somehow we two were hanging on to each other, and that was-- yeah.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, it didn't bring bad memories.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I tell you, frankly, I was thinking all my life, these soldiers were fighting for somebody else's [BACKGROUND NOISE] goodwill, life.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They came through from Russia, left their families, and they came to a hostile country, Hungary, where, all right, the Jews were there, to liberate them.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they were already on the way for years, these Russian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were frustrated.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They found grateful Jews who were kissing them and hugging them to liberate them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, of course, for them, they're not the most educated people-- for them it was the open door to go and rape us, or have sexual intercourse, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I looked at it from that point of view, and [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I haven't got bad feelings towards Russians, really and truly.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mentality to the whole-- yes, I have.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I haven't had, as I said, any hang-ups I have bad memories, and I was affected by the whole year or year and a half what we had concentrated, very bad time in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
